The paper focuses on distributed computation and communication complexity, which are core topics in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The paper also deals with graph optimization problems, which are typically studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of quantum computing and quantum communication puts the paper in the cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.QL (Quantum Physics) sub-categories.
